name: Damn the Torpedoes
description:
On August 5th, 1864 Admiral David Farragut threw caution to wind, yelled ‘Damn The Torpedoes’ and sent his Union fleet into the heavily fortified Mobile Bay to win the day.  Just like Admiral Farragut, some days you just need to say ‘Damn The Torpedoes’ and run full speed at life. Light up that cigar and pour yourself a drink because the gym will still be there tomorrow.

*1935 ZIPPO

* Stanley Flask

• Organic Cotton TGL Record Tote
